Title: A Very Simplistic, Universal, Lossless Code  
Author: David L. Neuhoff Paul C. Shields 
Address: Ann Arbor, MI 48109, USA  OH 43606, USA  
Affiliation: Electrical Engineering and Computer Science, University of Michigan,  Mathematics Department University of Toledo, Toledo,  
Abstract: A new, very simplistic, lossless source code is shown to be universal. With this code, given integers k and L, k &lt;&lt; L, a source sequence of length L is parsed into k-tuples; all distinct k-tuples are placed in a dictionary; the dictionary is encoded; and the index of each source k-tuple in the dictionary is encoded. It is shown in this paper that for any stationary, ergodic source, if k is optimized for the given L (for example, by trial and error), then as L tends to infinity, the rate of this very simplistic code tends to the entropy-rate of the source. Thus the code is universal. 
