Reference-contexts: INTRODUCTION Since universal lossless codes were discovered, a number of coding algorithms have been proposed and shown to be universal. Such codes (see <ref> [1] </ref> for a survey) have the property that for any stationary, ergodic source, their rate approaches the entropy-rate of the source as some parameter, such as blocklength, increases. The goals of such work include finding universal codes that minimize quantities such as redundancy, complexity and blocklength.
